Xiaomi has launched its latest Redmi smartphone – the Note 7. The device’s standout feature is a 48MP camera, which is one of two sensors that form part of a dual-lens rear camera system. The other sensor is a 5MP unit. Other features of the device include a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor, a display notch, a 13MP front-facing camera, and a colorful chassis. The screen is a 6.3-inch 1080p display, which is powered by a Snapdragon 660 processor and 4,000mAh battery. Xiaomi said that while the device’s primary port is a USB-C connection, the smartphone will also feature a headphone jack – not ditching the port like many other brands have done. The Redmi Note 7 will initially be available in China at the following prices: